## 1. Core System Registers (BP35 / Node)
These registers are used to pull raw data or trigger physical relays on the main power board.
BLE Reg (Hex),Dec,Name,Description / Payload
0x61,97,Battery Current,Signed Int16 (mA). Negative = Discharge.
0x62,98,Battery Voltage,Uint16 (mV). Current reading: ~13.16V.
0x63,99,Solar Voltage,Input voltage from the MPPT controller.
0x64,100,Solar Current,Charging current from solar panels (mA).
0x66,102,State of Charge,Battery percentage (0–100%).
0x67,103,Charge Power,[NEW] Internal charger effort/AC charge (Watts/mA).
0x6A,106,Battery Capacity,Uint32 (mAh). Your system is set to 300Ah.
0x6B,107,Aux/Car Voltage,Anderson Plug input. 0.20V = Disconnected/Off.
0x6C,108,Total Load,[NEW] Total system consumption (mA). Always positive.
0x70,112,System Health,"Status. 0x0A = Normal, 0x01 = Fault."

## 2. Control & Switch Registers
To use these, your msg_type in the script should be 6 (Command/Set).
BLE Reg (Hex),Dec,Name,Payload Status Code Meaning
0x40 - 0x48,64-72,Generic Outputs,"00=Off, 15=Standby, 2A=Fault/Parasitic."
0x49,73,Light 1,Relay status for Light Circuit 1.
0x4A,74,Light 2,Relay status for Light Circuit 2.
0x4B,75,Light 3,Relay status for Light Circuit 3.
0x4C,76,Pump 1,Water Pump 1 Relay.
0x4D,77,Pump 2,Water Pump 2 Relay (if equipped).

## 3. Tank & Environment Registers
These are usually broadcast as notifications once the bridge is "poked."
BLE Reg (Hex),Dec,Name,Description / Payload
0x03,3,Console Unlock,"[0x40, 0x10, 0x01] - Required to start BLE stream."
0x80,128,Water Tanks,"4-byte array. 05 = 100%, 01 = 0%."
0x83,131,Temperature,"Byte 1: Index (1=Ext, 2=Int). Byte 5-6: Temp in mC."
0x00,0,Version Info,"Firmware string (e.g., 41 12 61 32 37)."

## 4. The "Hidden" Shunt Registers (BC300)
If you have a BC300 External Shunt, it has its own ID in the system but uses the same register logic.
Target ID,BLE Reg (Hex),Name,Description
25116,0x1CE,Bridge HB,[NEW] BLE Gateway / Wi-Fi heartbeat broadcast.
16,0x69,Charge Mode,Current charging profile (Bulk/Float/LVD).
16,0x6F,System Timer,Internal uptime clock.
